During this pandemic we have all faced challenges. From teachers losing close family members to students having parents diagnosed with COVID-19 we have all been affected in one way or another.
This video was a way to bring a smile on the faces of everyone at our school! To see our amazing students happy and thriving despite living through these uncertain times.
After being in quarantine, distance learning, and having to adjust to a new way of life, we hope this brings you and other schools and families a little joy! We know that we can make it through anything by staying strong and sticking together!

post_text: Managing snacking habits for kids during this time
shared_text:
Jen Hallstrom
March 17 at 8:59 PM ¬∑

I keep seeing these posts about kiddos wanting to eat all day while they are home. This was my solution! Each child has their own colored basket. In the morning I put their snacks in it for the day, when those snacks are gone they don‚Äôt get any more. It makes them stop and think do I really need a snack? I also put their cup for the day in there because I‚Äôm not washing 50 cups a day! Hahaha!

Edit to add: I didn‚Äôt think I had to say this but my children eat breakfast, lunch and dinner. They are well fed and I don‚Äôt starve them üòÇ sad I even have to say that. Also in no way shape or form am I fat shaming my children ü§¶‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è I just don‚Äôt have the luxury of spending $400 on just snacks for a week ü§∑‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è

https://www.facebook.com/The-JEN-Life-103471964629559/

In response to those parents who have questions regarding the stricter monitoring of the bathrooms on the upper floors:

Students have been filming Tic Tok videos in the restroom on the 7th floor

Students have been writing graffiti in the bathroom on the 7th floor

Students are on FILM on our video surveillance wandering the hallways and violating other people‚Äôs book bags and belongings.

THIS IS WHY aside from the 2 health breaks they take as a class, students can sign out 2 additional times a day for bathroom needs.

This is for accountability and is a regular school practice across the country.

If there is a child with more needs for accessibility, please feel free to send a doctor‚Äôs note

If you have questions, please ask your child if they have been a part of the flash mobs of TikToks we have in our possession that were filmed INSIDE our school during SCHOOL HOURS in which they are supposed to be in class

‚Äî-the Management
